            <h4 class="text-center">Our Roots: </h4>
            <p class="text-center">In 1988, Vidan Lazic went and purchased Harczaks Sausages, a small polish meat company located in the northwest of Chicago. An immigrant with past work experience in Vienna sausage company in Austria, the next part seemed easy. Make good product and get it out there. Vidan made a good product that was in pretty high demand at the time, many businesses opted to purchase their polish sausage from Harczaks sausages and buisness was great for years. Around the mid 90s, his son Alekandar Lazic took over the buisness when he got sick to keep it afloat. Aleks continued to have a large role in the buisness even after Vidan recovered and buisness continued as usual. The 2008 Housing Crisis and Recession had a big impact on buisness as many of the big customers opted to close amid the recession. Around that time, Vidan got sick again. As he had no hopes of recovering this time, Aleks took over the buisness permanently.  </p>
